centered arenas, Uncertain Tastes argues that the experience of food itself-symbolic, sensuous, social, and material-is intrinsically characterized by multiple and frequently conflicting layers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCulture conflictxKenyaxSamburu District. 0aCulture conflictzKenyazSamburu District. 0aFood habitsxKenyaxSamburu District. 0aFood habitszKenyazSamburu District. 0aFood preferencesxKenyaxSamburu District. 0aFood preferenceszKenyazSamburu District. 0aFoodxSymbolic aspectsxKenyaxSamburu District. 0aFoodxSymbolic aspectszKenyazSamburu District. 0aSamburu (African people)xDomestic animals. 0aSamburu (African people)xFood. 0aSamburu (African people)xSocial conditions. 0aSocial changexKenyaxSamburu District. 0aSocial changezKenyazSamburu District. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944824423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520944824.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles